### Secondary: Stacked-model discrepancy test

As a complement to the TOST equivalence tests above, we pool both datasets and
estimate a `condition × source` interaction. The interaction term for each
intervention directly estimates the human–clone ATE discrepancy and provides
a conventional (directional) inferential test alongside the equivalence tests.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Stack and test condition × source interaction for the primary outcome.
# Positive estimate_h > estimate_l → clone underestimates; negative → overestimates.
stacked_primary <- run_stacked_model(human_data, llm_data,
                                     outcome = "trust_multidimensional")
```
:::



::: {#tbl-rq1-stacked .cell tbl-cap='Stacked-model discrepancy estimates for the primary outcome. Each row is one intervention; estimate = ATE_human − ATE_clone from the condition × source interaction.'}

```{.r .cell-code}
stacked_primary |>
  select(Condition = condition, Estimate = estimate,
         `95% CI low` = conf.low, `95% CI high` = conf.high,
         `p (adj)` = p.value_adjusted, ` ` = significant_adjusted) |>
  gt() |>
  fmt_number(columns = c(Estimate, `95% CI low`, `95% CI high`), decimals = 3) |>
  fmt_number(columns = `p (adj)`, decimals = 3)
```

