### RQ4b: Demographic predictability — stereotyping test

We regress the primary outcome on all six demographic moderators plus condition
fixed effects separately for humans and clones. A substantially higher R² in clones
indicates over-reliance on demographic stereotypes (mapping demographics to responses
too mechanically). We also compare individual demographic coefficients side by side.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pred_test <- compare_demographic_predictability(
  human_data, llm_data,
  outcome    = "trust_multidimensional",
  predictors = moderators_cat
)
```
:::



::: {#tbl-rq4b-rsq .cell tbl-cap='R² from regressing the primary outcome on demographics + condition FE, separately for humans and clones. Clone R² >> human R² signals demographic stereotyping.'}

```{.r .cell-code}
